headline: Why Prudential (PRU) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of financial services giant Prudential Financial (NYSE:PRU) jumped 2.7% in the morning session after the company reported third-quarter results that surpassed Wall Street's expectations for both profit and revenue. The financial services giant posted adjusted earnings of $4.26 per share, easily clearing analysts' consensus estimates of $3.72.
